<%- include('partials/header') %>
<style>
    /* Reset */
    * {
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
        box-sizing: border-box;
    }

    body {
        font-family: 'Poppins', sans-serif;
        background: #f8fafc;
        color: #1e293b;
        line-height: 1.6;
    }

    /* Navbar */
    nav {
        display: flex;
        justify-content: space-between;
        align-items: center;
        background: #1e293b;
        padding: 1rem 2rem;
        position: sticky;
        top: 0;
        z-index: 1000;
    }

    nav h2 {
        color: #fff;
        font-size: 1.5rem;
    }

    nav ul {
        list-style: none;
        display: flex;
        gap: 2rem;
    }

    nav ul li a {
        color: #fff;
        text-decoration: none;
        font-weight: 500;
        transition: color 0.3s ease;
    }

    nav ul li a:hover {
        color: #6838f8;
    }

    /* Hero Section */
    .hero {
        text-align: center;
        padding: 4rem 2rem;
        background: linear-gradient(to right, #647fed, #1518d3);
        color: #fff;
        border-radius: 0 0 2rem 2rem;
    }

    .hero h1 {
        font-size: 2.5rem;
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    .hero p {
        font-size: 1.2rem;
    }

    /* Content */
    .content {
        width: 90%;
        max-width: 1100px;
        margin: 3rem auto;
    }

    .content h2 {
        margin: 2rem 0 1rem;
        color: #1e293b;
        font-size: 1.8rem;
        border-left: 5px solid #38bdf8;
        padding-left: 10px;
    }

    /* Card Container */
    .card-container {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
        gap: 2rem;
        margin: 2rem 0;
    }

    .card {
        background: #fff;
        padding: 2rem;
        border-radius: 1rem;
        box-shadow: 0 6px 16px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        transition: transform 0.3s ease, box-shadow 0.3s ease;
    }

    .card:hover {
        transform: translateY(-8px);
        box-shadow: 0 12px 24px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.15);
    }

    .card h3 {
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
        color: #2563eb;
    }

    .card ul {
        list-style: disc;
        padding-left: 1.2rem;
        color: #475569;
    }

    .content ul {
        margin-left: 1.5rem;
        color: #475569;
    }
</style>

<!-- Navbar -->
<nav>
    <h2>Data Privacy Hub</h2>
    
</nav>

<!-- Hero Section -->
<section class="hero">
    <h1>Data Privacy & Protection in Education</h1>
    <p>Safeguarding student information in academic environments</p>
</section>
    <section class="content">
        <h1>Privacy Laws and Regulations in Education</h1>
        
        <h2>GDPR (General Data Protection Regulation)</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Special protections for children's data</li>
            <li>Requires verifiable parental consent for under-16s</li>
            <li>Right to be forgotten applies to educational records</li>
            <li>Data protection impact assessments required for educational processing</li>
            <li>Applies to international students from EU countries</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2>New Zealand Privacy Act 2020 - Educational Applications</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Principle 5: Secure storage of student records</li>
            <li>Principle 6: Student rights to access their educational information</li>
            <li>Principle 9: Limiting retention of student data</li>
            <li>Principle 11: Restrictions on disclosing student information</li>
            <li>Special considerations for sensitive information in educational contexts</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2>FERPA (Family Educational Rights and Privacy Act)</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Grants parents access to their children's education records</li>
            <li>Limits disclosure of student information without consent</li>
            <li>Allows parents to request record corrections</li>
            <li>Provides right to opt out of directory information sharing</li>
            <li>Contains exceptions for educational research and emergencies</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2>Case Study: University discloses student's location to Police</h2>
        <p>In 2008, a New Zealand university disclosed a student's examination details to police due to mental health concerns about the student's firearms license. This case highlights the balance between privacy and safety concerns in educational settings.</p>
    </section>
